Loopback-only discovery mode for Ableton Link.

Adds a single runtime atomic flag that, when set, causes the platform IP
interface scanner to return only loopback addresses. Link's internal
InterfaceScanner picks up the change on its next periodic scan (default
~5 s); a disable/enable cycle forces immediate rebind.

When the flag is false (default), upstream behaviour is bit-identical
to unmodified Link. Wire protocol unchanged. Public Link / LinkAudio
API surface unchanged. SuperSonic toggles the flag via
SuperClock::setLinkVisibility.

Targets the platform interface scanners so every platform honours the flag:
  include/ableton/platforms/posix/ScanIpIfAddrs.hpp   (macOS, Linux)
  include/ableton/platforms/windows/ScanIpIfAddrs.hpp (Windows)
Pinned to Link-4.0.

--- a/include/ableton/platforms/posix/ScanIpIfAddrs.hpp
+++ b/include/ableton/platforms/posix/ScanIpIfAddrs.hpp
@@ -20,7 +20,9 @@
 #pragma once

 #include <ableton/discovery/AsioTypes.hpp>
+#include <algorithm>
 #include <arpa/inet.h>
+#include <atomic>
 #include <ifaddrs.h>
 #include <map>
 #include <net/if.h>
@@ -70,6 +72,17 @@

 } // namespace detail

+// SUPERSONIC PATCH: runtime flag to constrain Link discovery to loopback only.
+// When true, ScanIpIfAddrs filters returned address list to loopback only, so
+// Link rebinds discovery/multicast/unicast sockets to lo0 (127.0.0.1). Default
+// false = upstream behaviour. Toggled by SuperClock::setLinkVisibility; takes
+// effect on the next InterfaceScanner tick (or immediately if Link is
+// disabled/re-enabled around the toggle).
+inline std::atomic<bool>& loopbackOnly()
+{
+  static std::atomic<bool> flag{false};
+  return flag;
+}

 // Posix implementation of ip interface address scanner
 struct ScanIpIfAddrs
@@ -126,6 +139,16 @@
         }
       });

+    // SUPERSONIC PATCH: filter to loopback only if requested. No-op (addrs
+    // unchanged) when flag is false.
+    if (loopbackOnly().load(std::memory_order_relaxed))
+    {
+      addrs.erase(std::remove_if(addrs.begin(), addrs.end(),
+                                 [](const discovery::IpAddress& a)
+                                 { return !a.is_loopback(); }),
+                  addrs.end());
+    }
+
     return addrs;
   };
 };

